<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4685559>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 6. Log-ratio plot of selected osteological measurements (see Table 62) of Gallinula disneyi and living and recently extinct species of native-hens Tribonyx. The standard species is Gallinula ventralis. Abbreviations are co, coracoid; h, humerus; ca, carpometacarpus; f, femur; tb, tibiotarsus; tm, tarsometatarsus; dlc, depth of condylus lateralis; dmc, depth of condylus medialis; dt3, depth of trochlea metatarsi III; dt4, depth of trochlea metatarsi IV; dw, distal width; paf, processus acrocoracoideus to facies articularis humeralis; pd, proximal depth; pw, proximal width; tl, total length." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4685559/files/figure.png" .

